 attracted to men, but are wary of emotional attachment with women; and others view sex with men—as opposed to women—as a more acceptable form of extramarital sexual behavior.Taking us inside the lives of straight white men who have sex with other men, Still Straight shows us that heterosexuality in rural America is not always, in fact, what it seems.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aGay menxIdentity. 0aHeterosexual menzUnited States. 0aMenxIdentity. 0aMen, WhitexSexual behaviorzUnited States. 0aRural gay menzUnited States. 0aRural menxSexual behaviorzUnited States. 0aWhite peoplexSexual behaviorzUnited States. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / Marriage & Family.2bisacsh  aAge.  aAging.  aBiphobia.  aBisexual erasure.  aBisexual.  aBud-sex.  aFamily.  aFriendship.  aGay.  aGender.  aHeterosexuality.  aHomophobia.  aLGBT.  aLove.  aMarriage.  aMasculinity.  aMen who have sex with men.  aMental health.  aRace.  aReligion.  aRomantic relationships.  aRural.  aSchool.  aSexuality.  aSports.  aStraight culture.  aWhiteness.40uhttps://doi.org/10.18574/nyu/9781479801121.001.000140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781479801121423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781479801121/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles